@startuml autenticacion
title CU-00: Iniciar Sesión y Gestión de Sesión

actor "Usuario" as User
participant "Navegador" as Browser
participant "LoginView\n(users/views.py)" as Login
participant "Usuario Model\n(users/models.py)" as UserModel
participant "TokenValidacion\n(users/models.py)" as Token
participant "Email Service\n(users/utils.py)" as EmailService
participant "Django Sessions" as Session
participant "config/urls.py\nRedirect" as Redirect

== CU-00.1: Validar Credenciales ==

User -> Browser: Navegar a /login/
Browser -> Login: GET /login/
Login --> Browser: Renderizar formulario login
User -> Browser: Ingresar email + contraseña

Browser -> Login: POST /login/ (email, password)
Login -> Login: Normalizar email (lower, strip)
Login -> UserModel: authenticate(email, password)
alt Credenciales válidas
    UserModel --> Login: Usuario autenticado
    Login -> Session: create_session(user)
    Login -> Login: Obtener tipo_usuario del usuario
    Login -> Login: Redirigir según rol
    alt Es CIUDADANO
        Login --> Browser: Redirect /perfil/
    else Es GESTOR_ECA
        Login --> Browser: Redirect /punto-eca/
    else Es ADMIN
        Login --> Browser: Redirect /panel_admin/
    end
else Credenciales inválidas
    UserModel --> Login: None
    Login --> Browser: Redirect /login/ + error message
end

== EXT-43: Recuperar Contraseña ==

User -> Browser: Olvidé mi contraseña
Browser -> Login: GET /login/recuperar/enviar/
Login --> Browser: Formulario ingresar email
User -> Browser: Ingresar email

Browser -> Login: POST /login/recuperar/enviar/
Login -> UserModel: buscar usuario por email
Login -> Token: generar_token(email, tipo="recuperacion")
note right: Token 8 caracteres\nexpira en TOKEN_EXPIRATION_MINUTES\nmax 5 intentos
Token --> Login: Token generado
Login -> EmailService: enviar_correo_recuperacion(email, token)
EmailService --> Login: Email enviado
Login --> Browser: Redirect /login/recuperar/validar/ + mensaje

User -> Browser: Ingresar código de verificación
Browser -> Login: POST /login/recuperar/validar/
Login -> Token: validar_token(email, token)
Token -> Token: Verificar expiración\n+ incrementar intentos
alt Token válido
    Token --> Login: Token válido
    Login --> Browser: Redirect /login/recuperar/cambiar/
else Token inválido o expirado
    Token --> Login: Token inválido
    Login --> Browser: Error + reintentar
end

User -> Browser: Ingresar nueva contraseña
Browser -> Login: POST /login/recuperar/cambiar/ (password, confirm)
Login -> Login: Validar coincidencia de contraseñas
Login -> UserModel: set_password(new_password)
Login -> Token: marcar_como_validado()
Login --> Browser: Redirect /login/ + "Contraseña actualizada"

== CU-00.3: Cerrar Sesión ==

User -> Browser: Cerrar sesión
Browser -> Login: GET /logout/
Login -> Session: flush()
Login --> Browser: Redirect /login/

@enduml
